Fault tolerance</keyword><keyword weight="0.46956">Point-to-point</keyword><keyword weight="0.47923">Message passing</keyword><keyword weight="0.45797">Distributed computing</keyword><keyword weight="0.49276">Network interface</keyword><keyword weight="0.48982">Scalability</keyword><keyword weight="0.46629">Embedded system</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>TEG is a new component-based methodology for point-to-point messaging. Developed as part of the Open MPI project, TEG provides a configurable fault-tolerant capability for high-performance messaging that utilizes multi-network interfaces where available. Initial performance comparisons with other MPI implementations show comparable ping-pong latencies, but with bandwidths up to 30% higher.</abstract></paper>